"Barbosa R.I., Fearnside P.M.","Pasture burning in Amazonia: Dynamics of residual biomass and the storage and release of aboveground carbon",1996,"Journal of Geophysical Research Atmospheres","101","20",,"25847","25857",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0343941919&partnerID=40&md5=7ce9dc2a6678c61877b55bc7f0b154ce","Núcleo de Pesq. de Roraima, Inst. Nac. de Pesq. da Amazonia, Boa Vista, Roraima, Brazil; Coordenadoria de Pesq. em Ecologia, Inst. Nac. de Pesq. da Amazonia, Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil; Núcleo de Pesq. de Roraima, Inst. Nac. de Pesq. da Amazonia, C. P. 96, 69301-970 Boa Vista, Roraima, Brazil; Coordenadoria de Pesq. em Ecologia, Inst. Nac. de Pesq. da Amazonia, C. P. 478, 69011-970 Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil","Barbosa, R.I., Núcleo de Pesq. de Roraima, Inst. Nac. de Pesq. da Amazonia, Boa Vista, Roraima, Brazil, Núcleo de Pesq. de Roraima, Inst. Nac. de Pesq. da Amazonia, C. P. 96, 69301-970 Boa Vista, Roraima, Brazil; Fearnside, P.M., Coordenadoria de Pesq. em Ecologia, Inst. Nac. de Pesq. da Amazonia, Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil, Coordenadoria de Pesq. em Ecologia, Inst. Nac. de Pesq. da Amazonia, C. P. 478, 69011-970 Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil","Aboveground biomass in cattle pasture converted from tropical dense forest was studied both before and after reburning in Brazilian Amazonia. In a 7-year-old pasture studied in Apiaú, Roraima, the aboveground dry weight of biomass (live plus dead) exposed to burning consisted of 96.3 t ha-1 of original forest remains, 6.2 t ha-1 of secondary successional vegetation (woody invaders in the pasture), and 8.0 t ha-1 of pasture grass (carbon contents 48.2%, 45.4%, and 42.2%, respectively). In terms of carbon, burning efficiencies for these three categories were 13.2%, 66.7% and 94.6%, respectively. Net charcoal formation was 0.35 t C ha-1 or 0.63% of the carbon exposed to the reburn, while the total accumulated since conversion (including the initial burn) is estimated at 2.3 t ha-1 (1.82% of the predeforestation aboveground biomass carbon stock). The dynamics of the original forest remains were represented in simulations that included parameters such as charcoal formation, burning efficiency and carbon concentration in different biomass components. Releases from initial burning of the cleared forest (44.0 t C ha-1) plus releases over the course of the succeeding decade through combustion (12.5 t C ha-1) and decay (51.5 t C ha-1) total 92% of the original forest biomass carbon (126 t C ha-1). Of biomass carbon remaining after the initial burn (84.3 t C ha-1), 76.0% is released: 61.1% through decay and 14.9% through combustion in reburns, while 1.2% is net conversion to charcoal in the reburns. These results indicate an amount of charcoal accumulation that is smaller than some carbon calculations have assumed, therefore suggesting a greater impact on global warming from conversion of forest to pasture.",,"biomass; burning; carbon emission; carbon storage; pasture; Brazil, Roraima State, Apiau",,,,,,"Barbosa, R.I., (1994) Efeito Estufa na Amazônia: Estimativa da Biomassa e a Quantificação do Estoque e Liberação de Carbono na Queima de Pastagens Convertidas de Florestas Tropicals em Roraima, Brasil, 85p. , Masters thesis, Inst. Nac. de Pesquisas da Amazônia, Univ. Fed. do Amazonas, Manaus, Brazil; Bogdonoff, P., Detwiler, R.P., Hall, C.A.S., Land use changes and carbon exchange in the tropics, III, Structure, basic equations, and sensitivity analysis of the model (1985) Environ. Manage. N.Y., 9 (4), pp. 345-354; Buschbacher, R.J., (1984) Changes in Productivity and Nutrient Cycling Following Conversion of Amazon Rainforest to Pasture, 193p. , Ph.D. dissertation, Univ. of Ga., Athens; Crutzen, P.J., Andreae, M.O., Biomass burning in the tropics: Impact on atmospheric chemistry and biogeochemical cycles (1990) Science, 250, pp. 1669-1678; Fahnestock, G.R., Carbon input to the atmosphere from forest fires (1979) Science, 204, pp. 209-210; Fearnside, P.M., (1986) Human Carrying Capacity of the Brazilian Rainforest, 293p. , Columbia Univ. Press, New York; Fearnside, P.M., Greenhouse gas contributions from deforestation in Brazilian Amazonia (1991) Global Biomass Burning: Atmospheric, Climatic, and Biospheric Implications, pp. 92-105. , edited by J. S. Levine, MIT Press, Cambridge, Mass; Fearnside, P.M., (1992) Greenhouse Gas Emissions from Deforestation in the Brazilian Amazon, Carbon Emissions and Sequestration in Forests: Case Studies from Developing Countries, 2, 73p. , Rep. LBL-32758, Lawrence Berkeley Lab., Berkeley, Ca; Fearnside, P.M., Ferraz, J., A conservation gap analysis of Brazil's Amazonian vegetation (1995) Conserv. Biol., 9 (5), pp. 1134-1147; Fearnside, P.M., Guimarães, W.M., Carbon uptake by secondary forests in Brazilian Amazonia (1996) For. Ecol. Manage., 80, pp. 35-46; Fearnside, P.M., Leal Filho, N., Fernandes, F.M., Rainforest burning and the global carbon budget: Biomass, combustion efficiency and charcoal formation in the Brazilian Amazon (1993) J. Geophys. Res., 98 (D9), pp. 16,733-16,743; Goudriaan, J., Ketner, P., A simulation study for the global carbon cycle, including man's impact on the biosphere (1984) Clim. Change, 6, pp. 167-192; Hao, W.M., Liu, M.H., Crutzen, P.J., Estimates of annual and regional releases of CO<inf>2</inf> and other trace gases to the atmosphere from fires in the tropics, based on the FAO statistics for the period 1975-80 (1990) Fire in the Tropical Biota, pp. 440-462. , edited by J. G. Goldammer, Springer-Verlag, New York; Houghton, J.T., Meira Filho, L.G., Bruce, J., Lee, H., Callander, B.A., Haites, E., Harris, N., Maskell, K., (1994) Climate Change 1994: Radiative Forcing of Climate Change and An Evaluation of the IPCC IS92 Emission Scenarios, , Cambridge Univ. Press, New York; Houghton, R.A., Tropical deforestation and atmospheric carbon dioxide (1991) Clim. Change, 19, pp. 99-118; (1993) Mapa de Vegetação do Brasil, , scale 1: 5,000,000, Rio de Janeiro; Lameira, O.A., Coimbra, J.M., Levantamento e distribuição da precipitação em Roraima (1988) Pesqui. em Andamento, 12, 5p. , Empresa Bras. de Pesqui. Agropecuária/Serv. Nac. de Levantamento e Conserv. de Solo, Roraima, Brazil; (1975) Levantamento de Recursos Naturais, 8, 428p. , Rio de Janeiro; Robinson, J.M., On uncertainty in the computation of global emissions from biomass burning (1989) Clim. Change, 14, pp. 243-262; Saldarriaga, J.C., West, D.C., Tharp, M.L., Uhl, C., Long-term chronosequence of forest sucession in the upper Rio Negro of Colombia and Venezuela (1988) J. Ecol., 76, pp. 938-958; Santos, R.D., Gama, J.N.R.F., Soares, A.F., Levantamento de reconhecimento de baixa intensidade dos solos e avaliação da aptidão agrícola das terras do Projeto de Colonização Apiaú, Território Federal de Roraima (1982) Bol. de Pesqui., 14, 175p. , Empresa Bras. de Pesqui. Agropecuária/Serv. Nac. de Levantamento e Conserv. de Solo, Roraima, Brazil; Seiler, W., Crutzen, P.J., Estimates of gross and net fluxes of carbon between the biosphere and the atmosphere from biomass burning (1980) Clim. Change, 2, pp. 207-247; Wong, C.S., Atmospheric input of carbon dioxide from burning wood (1978) Science, 200, pp. 197-200","Fearnside, P.M.; Coordenadoria de Pesq. em Ecologia, Inst. Nac. de Pesq. da Amazonia, C. P. 478, 69011-970 Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil; email: pmfearn@cr-am.rnp.br",,,"Blackwell Publishing Ltd",,,,,01480227,,,,"English","J. Geophys. Res. D Atmos.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0343941919
